FBIS4-28994 "dreas115_n_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-115 Daily Report 12 Jun 1994 Vietnam Circular on Export Procedure Changes Issued Circular on Export Procedure Changes Issued BK1406091194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 1100 GMT 12 Jun 94 BK1406091194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network Vietnamese BFN [Text] The Ministry of Trade recently issued a circular which announces that effective from 1 July, the procedure of issuing export permits for a single trip will be abolished except in the following cases: -- Goods that are banned from export; -- Goods exported according to special plans; -- Goods of specifically managed industries; -- Special cases: goods for exchanging, semi-export goods, goods intended for labor-intensive produce exhibitions, and goods produced by foreign enterprises in Vietnam. Before the date this circular becomes effective nationwide, the Ministry of Trade and the Customs General Department will select a number of localities and production establishments which will experiment with the new procedures immediately in June. The circular will become effective nationwide on 1 July. The cancellation of the procedure of issuing export permits for a single trip will benefit business establishments in their export activities.
